    "• DuQM (Zhu et al, 2022).",
    "The DuQM dataset serves as a Chinese robust dataset for question matching, encompassing natural questions embedded with linguistic perturbations to assess the robustness of models in this particular task.",
    "DuQM comprises three overarching categories and thirteen subcategories of linguistic perturbation types, facilitating a comprehensive evaluation of diverse model performances.",
    "• LCQMC (Liu et al, 2018).",
    "The LCQMC dataset constitutes an extensive Chinese corpus designed for the matching of questions, with a distinct focus on aligning the intentions behind questions rather than achieving paraphrastic alignment of sentences."
